        &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/nav&gt;</pre>
</section>

<section id="footer">
    <h1>&lt;footer&gt;</h1>
    <p>Footers give a bit of padding and work well with buttons. On smaller resolutions, they stack up and go full-width.</p>
    <footer>
        <button>Submit</button>
    </footer>
    <pre>&lt;footer&gt;
    &lt;button&gt;Submit&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/footer&gt;</pre>
    <br>
    <p>Footers support multiple buttons and semantic classes:</p>
    <footer class="failure">
        <button class="warning">File a bug report</button>
        <button>Accept</button>
    </footer>
    <pre>&lt;footer class="failure"&gt;
    &lt;button class="warning"&gt;File a bug report&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button&gt;Accept&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/footer&gt;</pre>
</section>

